05626nam a22009255i 9781853596964DE-B159720211217065530.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211217t20032003enk    fo  d z      eng d  a2003008756  a97818535969647 a10.21832/97818535969642doi  a(DE-B1597)514084  a(OCoLC)1083629201  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  aenkcGB-BST00aLC3705b.M86 2003 4aLC3705b.M86 2003eb 7aLAN0090002bisacsh04a370.11722100aMultilingual Classroom Ecologies :bInter-relationship, Interactions and Ideologies /ced. by Angela Creese, Peter Martin. 1aBristol ;aBlue Ridge Summit : bMultilingual Matters, c[2003] 4c©2003  a1 online resource (152 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aBilingual Education & Bilingualism0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe theme of this book is the multilingual classroom and the interrelationships, interactions and ideologies that apply in such classrooms. Drawing on studies from different multilingual communities in different parts of the world, the volume demonstrates the complex nature of the multilingual classroom, and in so doing provides a number of interdisciplinary perspectives for an international audience. The contributions to the volume are located within an ecological framework, one that emphasises the inter-relationships between languages and their speakers in multilingual and multi-cultural classrooms, the dynamics of multilingual classroom interaction, and the positionings of classroom languages and their speakers in dominant educational discourses. There are three main themes interweaved throughout the book: Inter-relationships • Relationships between languages and their speakers in multilingual/multicultural classrooms. • The impact of educationally dominant languages on the ecologies of other languages. Interactions • The dynamics of multilingual classroom interaction for learning and teaching bilingually. • The discursive meetings and mergings of socially situated participants within multilingual classrooms. Ideology • The positionings of classroom languages and their speakers in dominant educational discourses/conversations. • The positionings of pedagogies, knowledge and participants in multilingual classrooms.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aEducation, BilingualvCongresses. 0aEducation, BilingualxCongresses. 0aLiteracyvCongresses. 0aLiteracyxCongresses. 0aMulticulturalismvCongresses. 0aMulticulturalismxCongresses. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  alanguage education.  amultilingualism.1 aArthur, Jo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoyd, Sally, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCreese, Angela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCreese, Angela, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHornberger, Nancy H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJaffe, Alexandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartin, Deirdre, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartin, Peter W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartin, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartin, Peter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMartin-Jones, Marilyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSaxena, Mukul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSkilton-Sylvester, Ellen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 200